    "Neurological examinations are also carried out to assess reflexes, muscle strength, coordination, and other elements of nervous system functioning (Galasko et al. 1990).",
    "AD-related alterations in the brain are discovered with the help of imaging tests like PET and MRI scans.",
    "While both MRI and PET can identify different brain regions, they do so using different methods and are used for specific purposes.",
    "MRI is primarily used for identifying structural abnormalities in brain, while PET is utilized to identify functional changes that occur in the brain.",
    "In some cases, both imaging techniques may be used together to furnish a more inclusive viewpoint of the brain and its functions."
